{
  "stem": "8.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because, even though we heard some rumors about Poland and Czechoslovakia and, and Yugoslavia-- I remember clearly when I heard that they took all these Jews to the Danube River, and they shot them, and they all fell into the river and they floated down the river, which became red from their blood.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I remember hearing that, but somehow I could not believe it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And, the Hungarian Jews were especially so isolated.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were kind of in between the more Western Jews and the Eastern Jews.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They did not speak Yiddish much, the Hungarian Jews, and they felt so patriotic.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I mean, my family had lived there for hundreds of years.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Although, my family from my mother's side comes from a very important family of the Horowitz-Margaretens with their genealogy going back all the way to 15th century.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "My immediate family my, grandfathers, my parents, and so on, they all lived in Hungary for many, many years.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And, when I went to school, even though it was a Jewish school, we sang the national anthem every morning.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So, it was very hard for us to believe, probably similar to German Jews, that something can happen to us because we were such good Hungarians.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And it was-- it was like an unreality.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So, when we heard about the, the Czechoslovakians and the, the Polish, we said, well, it must be because they were not good patriots.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Maybe they had done something.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, also, we did not hear anything what really happened.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We knew that they were shot and they were taken away, but nothing like Auschwitz or anything like that we heard about.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We also had some refugees from those countries, and they were illegally there in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
